The paper discusses a distributed graph database designed for efficient storage and processing of graph data on modern computing architectures. This topic falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Database (cs.DB), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Among these, cs.DB and cs.DC are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the design and implementation of distributed databases and graph processing systems. cs.DS is also a likely category as the paper discusses the optimization of data structures for efficient graph processing. cs.NI and cs.SI are less likely categories, but still relevant as the paper touches upon the communication and runtime layer of the distributed graph database and the value of extracting knowledge from interconnected data.
